Definition: designating or relating to a form of treatment of mental disorders that seeks to restore biochemical balance in the body with large doses of vitamins and minerals
Example: orthomolecular medicine; orthomolecular therapy
Synonyms: designating, or, relating, to, a, form, of, treatment, mental, disorders, that, seeks, restore, biochemical, balance, in, the, body, with, large, doses, vitamins, and, minerals, medicine, therapy
Category: adj.all
